### 3. `parseMarkdownToEvents(fileName, contents)`

Core parser for one `.md` file:

```js
function parseMarkdownToEvents(fileName, contents) {
  const dateObj = dateFromFilename(fileName);
  if (!dateObj) return [];

  const events = [];
  const lines = contents.split(/\r?\n/);

  const re = /^-\s*\[[ xX]?\]\s*(\d{3,4})\s*-\s*(\d{3,4})\s+(.+)$/;

  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
    const line = lines[i];
    const m = line.match(re);
    if (!m) continue;

    const [, startStr, endStr, summaryRaw] = m;
    const start = makeDateTime(dateObj, startStr);
    const end = makeDateTime(dateObj, endStr);
    if (!start || !end) continue;

    // Collect indented bullets / text that follow as description
    const details = [];
    let j = i + 1;
    while (j < lines.length) {
      const ln = lines[j];
      const trimmed = ln.trim();

      if (!trimmed) break; // blank line ends description block
      if (/^-\s*\[[ xX]?]/.test(ln)) break; // next top-level task

      if (/^\s+[-*]\s+/.test(ln)) {
        // Indented bullet
        details.push(trimmed.replace(/^[-*]\s+/, ''));
      } else if (/^\s+/.test(ln)) {
        // Any other indented text
        details.push(trimmed);
      } else {
        // Non-indented, non-task line → stop
        break;
      }
      j++;
    }

    let description = '';
    if (details.length) {
      description = details.join('\n');
    }

    events.push({
      summary: summaryRaw.trim(),
      location: '',
      description,
      start,
      end,
      fileName,
    });
  }
  return events;
}
```

Notes:

- Includes **both** `[x]` and `[ ]` tasks; the checkbox state is ignored – if needed you can branch here.
- Regex captures:
  - Group 1: start time (3–4 digits).
  - Group 2: end time.
  - Group 3: rest of the line (summary).
- The inner `while` loop collects indented bullets/text as description.

Possible customisations:

- Change the regex to require a specific emoji or tag in the task line.
- Inspect the checkbox to, for example, prefix incomplete tasks with `TODO:` in the summary.
- Extend the parser to read locations (`@ Location`) and store them in `location`.

