### 4. Recursive directory walk

```js
async function collectMarkdownFilesFromDir(dirHandle, eventsOut, filesCountRef) {
  for await (const [name, handle] of dirHandle.entries()) {
    if (handle.kind === 'file' && name.toLowerCase().endsWith('.md')) {
      filesCountRef.count++;
      const file = await handle.getFile();
      const text = await file.text();
      const events = parseMarkdownToEvents(name, text);
      eventsOut.push(...events);
    } else if (handle.kind === 'directory') {
      await collectMarkdownFilesFromDir(handle, eventsOut, filesCountRef);
    }
  }
}
```

- Recursively walks the folder tree starting at the root directory handle returned by `showDirectoryPicker()`. [web:23][web:36]
- Accumulates:
  - `eventsOut`: an array of all events found.
  - `filesCountRef.count`: total number of `.md` files processed.

If you want to limit scanning to a certain depth, you can add a `depth` parameter and stop when a limit is reached.

